  "original_title": "\u0d91\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dca\u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db4\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dc0\u0dda \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca  \u0d9a\u0ddd\u0da7\u0dd2 \u0db1\u0dc0\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd9\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Nine crores in the fire of Express Pearl ship",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The chairman of the Maritime Environment Protection Authority, lawyer Darshanee Lahandapura, said that nine million thirty-eight million fifty-seven thousand two hundred and ninety-three rupees have been spent so far to clean the coastline from Mannar to Hambantota Kirinda by removing the plastic and waste released by the ship M.V Express Pearl, which caught fire in Sri Lanka's waters. Mrs. said.",
        "Mrs. Lahandapura also said that it will take several more years to remove the plastic and chemicals released from the ship's containers and completely clean the coastline.",
        "She mentioned that 1600 metric tons of plastic beads and chemicals released from the ship have been deposited in warehouses acquired on rental basis in Pamunugama area and further steps will be taken based on legal advice.",
        "The container ship MV Express Pearl, which was carrying goods under the flag of Singapore, caught fire and sank 9 nautical miles from the port of Colombo on June 02 last year.",
        "The Chairperson of the Marine Environment Protection Authority said this in a discussion held at the Urban Development and Housing Ministry Auditorium in Setsiripa, Battaramulla."
      ],
